  "highlighted_cells": {
    "rf_nu":  {"t":"Nuclear — Enrichment (most acute strategic gap in the universe)","f":["fch","fgp","fgeo"],"b":"Centrus Energy (LEU) is the ONLY US company with active domestic uranium enrichment capacity. TENEX/Rosatom supplied ~28% of US SWU before the Prohibiting Russian Uranium Imports Act (2024). HALEU for SMRs/advanced reactors = essentially zero non-Russian supply — Centrus building from scratch with DoD/DOE support. Year 1-2 of a 10-year rebuild."},
    "rf_re":  {"t":"REE — Separation (single most acute geopolitical chokepoint)","f":["fch","fgp","fgeo"],"b":"China controls ~85-90% of global REE separation. Outside China: MP Materials (NdPr at Mountain Pass + Fort Worth TX magnet facility); Lynas Malaysia + Seadrift TX (DoD-funded, under construction). HREE (Dy, Tb) separation: essentially NO Western capacity at all. Most strategically urgent single processing gap in critical minerals globally."},
    "di_nu":  {"t":"Nuclear Power Operations — AI data center PPA template","f":["fgeo"],"b":"Constellation Energy (CEG — ~10% of US electricity). Microsoft Three Mile Island restart (2024) = 20yr PPA at ~$110/MWh for 24/7 carbon-free power. Template being replicated across CEG fleet. SMRs: GE-Hitachi BWRX-300 (Ontario Power 4-unit order — first Western commercial SMR contract); X-energy Xe-100 (Dow Chemical site); BWXT as components supplier."},
    "di_cu":  {"t":"Copper — Grid infrastructure & transformer bottleneck","f":["fgp"],"b":"Grid components: Hitachi Energy (world's largest LPT maker, multi-year backlog), ABB (ABBN), Eaton (ETN), GE Vernova (GEV). HV cables: Prysmian (PRY.MI), Nexans (NEX.PA) — 3-4yr backlog. Grid EPC: Quanta (PWR, ~40% US market). Transformer lead times: 2-4 years. Unprecedented simultaneous demand from AI DCs + EVs + grid hardening."},
    "rf_li":  {"t":"Lithium — Processing & cell manufacturing (Chinese chokehold)","f":["fch","fgeo"],"b":"~70% of global LiOH conversion is Chinese. Battery precursor (pCAM): Umicore, BASF, CNGR/Huayou (China dominant). Cells: CATL (~37%), BYD, Panasonic, Samsung SDI, LGES, SK On. IRA domestic content requirements forcing reshoring — 5-10yr lag. Arcadium (Rio Tinto) + Piedmont building non-Chinese conversion."},
    "pr_nu":  {"t":"Uranium Mining — extreme supply concentration","f":["fch","fgp","fgeo"],"b":"Cameco (CCO — world's highest-grade; ~15% global supply); Kazatomprom (KAP — ~40% global ISR; geopolitically ambiguous); Paladin (Langer Heinrich, Namibia); UEC (US ISR); Boss Energy (Australia). Top 3 = ~65% of global supply. Supply has not met demand since Fukushima (2011) — 12+ years of inventory drawdown."},
    "rr_cu":  {"t":"Copper — Royalty & streaming (best risk-adjusted exposure in the vertical)","f":[],"b":"FNV and WPM hold silver/gold streams at major copper mines — best risk-adjusted structure in the hard assets universe. WPM key streams: Antamina Ag (Peru), Salobo Au (Brazil), Constancia Ag (Peru). Streaming = Cu upside without capex, processing risk, or jurisdictional concentration. Sits above the Chinese smelting chokepoint entirely."},
    "pr_fert":{"t":"Fertilizers — Potash mining (allied-nation food security play)","f":["fgeo"],"b":"Nutrien (NTR — world's largest K producer + significant N+P; ONLY complete NPK company globally; Canpotex JV with Mosaic controls Canadian export logistics worldwide). Mosaic (MOS — Esterhazy K + Florida P mining). ICL Group (Israel — Dead Sea Works K + Rotem P). OCP Morocco (state-owned private, ~70% global phosphate reserves — the long-term chokepoint to monitor)."},
    "rc_li":  {"t":"Battery recycling — geopolitically domesticated supply","f":["fgeo"],"b":"Li-Cycle (LICY — hub+spoke hydromet; strategic asset); Redwood Materials (private — JB Straubel; DOE loan; major OEM partnerships). DoD + IRA funding flowing. Domesticated supply bypasses Chinese processing control. 2026-2030 is the inflection point as first generation of mass-market EVs reaches end-of-life."},
    "rf_nu2": {"t":"Nuclear Fuel Fabrication — sticky oligopoly at the final processing step","f":["fch"],"b":"Westinghouse (Brookfield-owned; Columbia SC + Springfields UK); Framatome (EDF subsidiary, France); GNF (GE-Hitachi + Toshiba JV, Wilmington NC). 5-7yr reactor qualification cycles = extremely sticky customer relationships. Once a utility qualifies a fuel supplier for a specific reactor design, they rarely switch."}
  },
